Author: Gateway#3763
Content:
[telegram] <At0micSwap> An Atomic Swap is a proposed feature in cryptocurrencies, that allows for the exchange of one cryptocurrency for another cryptocurrency without the need for a trusted third party. In traditional cryptocurrencies a trusted third party such as an cryptocurrency exchange is necessary to perform a swap of cryptocurrencies in order to prevent one party from sending a currency without receiving a currency in return.
Atomic swap give the crypto community a safe way to trade across different blockchains.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content:
[telegram] <Regnar> Nice little discussion happening on my twitter. Join in if you like, give your thoughts and opinions. The stances so far are 1. an altcoin project buying 6K KMD to secure 5.1% gains in KMD which is enough to pay for future dPoW yearly cost is a bad investment because other coins can get higher returns on that $9K investment. 
and 2. (mine) that speculative investing is not something you should risk your project on, that the valuation increase and decrease in the 6K KMD doesn't matter because regardless of the price, 300 KMD is needed to pay for dPoW. So that could be $300 or $300,000. So the investment to secure that yearly 300 KMD regardless of price protects against 51% attacks, and also against the upside cost of buying KMD at market price in the future everytime you need to pay for dPoW.
